This is a single metaphor delivered in a jejune, slapdash manner. I didn't really understand what the mountain was supposed to look like from the initial description (how is the  hypotenuse concave or convex?) until I backfilled it at the end. For this metaphor to work, the whole silhouette of the mountain has to change shape but it isn't clear if this happens.

It's also thematically unsatisfying for me that this piece is so short and devoid of tension when the anomaly and the economic crash are so gigantic.







